doctype html
html
  include partials/_head.pug
body
  include partials/_ribbon.pug
  main
    .container
      header
        div.logo
          img(src="./images/graaf.svg")
        p.slogan.
          <strong>Pure CSS grid overlays</strong> for designing
        p.sub-slogan.
          Just link the CSS that fits your grid or create your custom overlay

    section.try
      .container
        button(onClick="guideGrid(this); return false;" data-step="0") Try it
        p.description.
          This button will add the following code to the <code>head</code> HTML tag.
        pre.example
          code.
            &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://grids.graaf.space/793/10/16.css"&gt;

    section.custom
      .container
        h2 Grids
        p.description.
          Now, You can create your <a href="#custom-grids">custom grid overlays</a> using the new
          Graaf API. Just set your grid parameters in the path:

        p
          pre
            code.
              &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://grids.graaf.space/WIDTH/COLUMNS/GUTTER.css"&gt;
              &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://grids.graaf.space/793/10/16.css"&gt;

    section.predefined
      .container
        h3 The collection
        p.
          You can use a predefined grid overlay from the collection:

        table.grids(cellspacing="0")
          include partials/_table_head.pug
          tbody
            each grid, i in currentGrids
              tr
                td= grid.name
                td.row-center= grid.width + 'px'
                td.row-center= grid.columns
                td.row-center= grid.gutter + 'px'
                td
                  a(href=grid.url + '?v=' + version)= grid.filename

    include partials/_usage.pug

  include partials/_footer.pug
  include partials/_ga.pug
